OL,3,CTeenager campaigns for better safety
OL,4,Cafter being left in school during fire
OL,6,FA teenage boy who was left alone
OL,7,Fupstairs during a school fire because
OL,8,Fthere was no safe way to get him out
OL,9,Fthe building has launched a campaign
OL,10,Fto improve fire safety for disabled
OL,11,Fstudents.
OL,13,FLucas Vezza-O'Brien, 16, who has
OL,14,Fcerebral palsy and uses a wheelchair,
OL,15,Fsays he was terrified when smoke began
OL,16,Fto fill the corridor at his school in
OL,17,FHyde, Greater Manchester, in November
OL,18,F2024.
