OL,3,CTeenager campaigns for better safety
OL,4,Cafter being left in school during fire
OL,6,FLucas said the school followed the
OL,7,Fcurrent legislation. He said: "The
OL,8,Ffire service told the school 'leave
OL,9,Fthe wheelchair users' and we'll come
OL,10,Fto evacuate them from the building."
OL,12,FLucas told Good Morning Britain about
OL,13,Fhis campaign for all schools to have
OL,14,Fevacuation chairs for students who use
OL,15,Fwheelchairs
OL,17,FThe fire turned out to be minor, but
OL,18,Fthe scare has sparked a powerful
OL,19,Fcampaign. The teenager is now calling
OL,20,Ffor evacuation chairs to be made a
OL,21,Flegal requirement in every school.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
